H0.text: Who was the first Englishman to lead an expedition to circumnavigate the earth by sea, and died of dysentery in the West Indies 16 years later. Thomas Cavendish

H1.text: Who was the first Englishman to lead an expedition to circumnavigate the earth by sea, and died of dysentery in the West Indies 16 years later. George Vancouver

H2.text: Who was the first Englishman to lead an expedition to circumnavigate the earth by sea, and died of dysentery in the West Indies 16 years later. James Cook

H3.text: Who was the first Englishman to lead an expedition to circumnavigate the earth by sea, and died of dysentery in the West Indies 16 years later. Draque

A4.text: Cavendish's own successful voyage, between 1586 and 1588, was the first deliberately planned circumnavigation.

A5.text: Cavendish later set out for a second raid and circumnavigation but was not as fortunate and died at sea in 1592, at the age of 31.

A6.text: Thomas Cavendish completed his circumnavigation between 1586 and 1588 in record timeâ€”in two years and 49 days.

A7.text: Captain James Cook became the first navigator to record three circumnavigations through the Pacific aboard the Endeavour from 1769 to 1771 and Resolution from 1772 to 1779.
